sql:
SELECT COUNT(usage_id) 
FROM cookie_usage 
WHERE last_used = '2023-05-01' AND average_session_duration > 300;

external_knowledge:
- "spread their digital footprint" refers to cookies that are being used for tracking;
- "marked for retirement" refers to cookies that have been opted out by the user (opt_out_status = 1);
- "digital guardians" refers to the providers of the tracking cookies.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cookie_id) 
FROM tracking_logs 
WHERE interaction_type = 'revoked';

external_knowledge:
- 'Marketing cookies' are used to track user behavior for advertising purposes;
- 'Consented interactions' refer to user interactions where the user has explicitly agreed to the use of the cookie;
- 'Google' is a major provider of tracking cookies.

- The correlation coefficient measures the strength and direction of the linear relationship between two variables;
- A correlation coefficient close to 1 indicates a strong positive relationship, while a coefficient close to -1 indicates a strong negative relationship;
- A correlation coefficient close to 0 indicates no linear relationship.

- 'digital consent withdrawn' refers to the user revoking their consent for cookies;
- 'opt-out status is set to true' means the user has chosen to opt out of cookie tracking;
- 'more than one interaction occurred on the same day' indicates that the same cookie had multiple revocation interactions on a single day.

sql:
